$ Examples for Socket.cpp

  → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/Socket_cpp/simple-client connects to → www.renenyffenegger.ch, port 80, and GETs its front page.

  → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/Socket_cpp/echo-server opens a port on
  2000 and waits for incoming connections. Each connection is answered with the
  same line as was written (echoed).


  → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/Socket_cpp/proxy listens on a specified port and relays income
  traffic to a specified server/port.

  → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/Socket_cpp/Message-distributor distributes messages to any number of clients.

{ Compiling #compiling-socket-examples

  { compile.ming.bat

    With Mingw, the examples can be compiled with the following bat file:
    gh|Socket.cpp|/examples/compile.ming.bat||

  }

}
